    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> It sounds like that that cli is the special-case or do other eth2 clients also require this flag?\r\n\r\nTeku does `--network mainnet`. Nimbus and Lighthouse haven't released their support yet.\r\n\r\nI'd expect that all clients that have a `--network` flag - which is Nimbus and will be Lighthouse when they rename `--testnet` - will add a `mainnet` option to that flag and simply default to it. Which makes combined tooling for main and test really easy.\r\n\r\nGeth indeed has no flag, it requires some user intervention to indicate \"not test\".",
