    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "After discussion on Discord, rationale for this change: Not having the flag makes my tooling more difficult, having it makes it easier.\r\n\r\nWithout the flag works, it's just extra steps. So instead of NETWORK= and then either medalla or mainnet, I'll need to duplicate prysm-base and have a prysm-base-main and prysm-base-test yml, because the docker-compose entrypoint right now assumes it can specify ${NETWORK}.\r\n\r\nI can work around it. I'd love it if I didn't have to.\r\n",
